84void RenderFlexibleBox::computeIntrinsicLogicalWidths(LayoutUnit& minLogicalWidth, LayoutUnit& maxLogicalWidth) const
85{
86 auto addScrollbarWidth = [&]() {
87 LayoutUnit scrollbarWidth(scrollbarLogicalWidth());
88 maxLogicalWidth += scrollbarWidth;
89 minLogicalWidth += scrollbarWidth;
90 };
91
92 if (shouldApplySizeContainment(*this)) {
93 addScrollbarWidth();
94 return;
95 }
96
97 LayoutUnit childMinWidth;
98 LayoutUnit childMaxWidth;
99 bool hadExcludedChildren = computePreferredWidthsForExcludedChildren(childMinWidth, childMaxWidth);
100
101 // FIXME: We're ignoring flex-basis here and we shouldn't. We can't start
102 // honoring it though until the flex shorthand stops setting it to 0. See
103 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=116117 and
104 // https://crbug.com/240765.
105 size_t numItemsWithNormalLayout = 0;
106 for (RenderBox* child = firstChildBox(); child; child = child->nextSiblingBox()) {
107 if (child->isOutOfFlowPositioned() || child->isExcludedFromNormalLayout())
108 continue;
109 ++numItemsWithNormalLayout;
110
111 LayoutUnit margin = marginIntrinsicLogicalWidthForChild(*child);
112
113 LayoutUnit minPreferredLogicalWidth;
114 LayoutUnit maxPreferredLogicalWidth;
115 computeChildPreferredLogicalWidths(*child, minPreferredLogicalWidth, maxPreferredLogicalWidth);
116
117 minPreferredLogicalWidth += margin;
118 maxPreferredLogicalWidth += margin;
119
120 if (!isColumnFlow()) {
121 maxLogicalWidth += maxPreferredLogicalWidth;
122 if (isMultiline()) {
123 // For multiline, the min preferred width is if you put a break between
124 // each item.
125 minLogicalWidth = std::max(minLogicalWidth, minPreferredLogicalWidth);
126 } else
127 minLogicalWidth += minPreferredLogicalWidth;
128 } else {
129 minLogicalWidth = std::max(minPreferredLogicalWidth, minLogicalWidth);
130 maxLogicalWidth = std::max(maxPreferredLogicalWidth, maxLogicalWidth);
131 }
132 }
133
134 if (!isColumnFlow() && numItemsWithNormalLayout > 1) {
135 LayoutUnit inlineGapSize = (numItemsWithNormalLayout - 1) * computeGap(GapType::BetweenItems);
136 maxLogicalWidth += inlineGapSize;
137 if (!isMultiline())
138 minLogicalWidth += inlineGapSize;
139 }
140
141 maxLogicalWidth = std::max(minLogicalWidth, maxLogicalWidth);
142
143 // Due to negative margins, it is possible that we calculated a negative
144 // intrinsic width. Make sure that we never return a negative width.
145 minLogicalWidth = std::max(0_lu, minLogicalWidth);
146 maxLogicalWidth = std::max(0_lu, maxLogicalWidth);
147
148 if (hadExcludedChildren) {
149 minLogicalWidth = std::max(minLogicalWidth, childMinWidth);
150 maxLogicalWidth = std::max(maxLogicalWidth, childMaxWidth);
151 }
152
153 addScrollbarWidth();
154}
155
156#define SET_OR_CLEAR_OVERRIDING_SIZE(box, SizeType, size) \
157 { \
158 if (size) \
159 box.setOverridingLogical##SizeType(*size); \
160 else \
161 box.clearOverridingLogical##SizeType(); \
162 }
163
164// RAII class which defines a scope in which overriding sizes of a box are either:
165// 1) replaced by other size in one axis if size is specified
166// 2) cleared in both axis if size == std::nullopt
167//
168// In any case the previous overriding sizes are restored on destruction (in case of
169// not having a previous value it's simply cleared).
170class OverridingSizesScope {
171public:
172 enum class Axis {
173 Inline,
174 Block,
175 Both
176 };
177
178 OverridingSizesScope(RenderBox& box, Axis axis, std::optional<LayoutUnit> size = std::nullopt)
179 : m_box(box)
180 , m_axis(axis)
181 {
182 ASSERT(!size || (axis != Axis::Both));
183 if (axis == Axis::Both || axis == Axis::Inline) {
184 if (box.hasOverridingLogicalWidth())
185 m_overridingWidth = box.overridingLogicalWidth();
186 SET_OR_CLEAR_OVERRIDING_SIZE(m_box, Width, size);
187 }
188 if (axis == Axis::Both || axis == Axis::Block) {
189 if (box.hasOverridingLogicalHeight())
190 m_overridingHeight = box.overridingLogicalHeight();
191 SET_OR_CLEAR_OVERRIDING_SIZE(m_box, Height, size);
192 }
193 }
194 ~OverridingSizesScope()
195 {
196 if (m_axis == Axis::Inline || m_axis == Axis::Both)
197 SET_OR_CLEAR_OVERRIDING_SIZE(m_box, Width, m_overridingWidth);
198
199 if (m_axis == Axis::Block || m_axis == Axis::Both)
200 SET_OR_CLEAR_OVERRIDING_SIZE(m_box, Height, m_overridingHeight);
201 }
202
203private:
204 RenderBox& m_box;
205 Axis m_axis;
206 std::optional<LayoutUnit> m_overridingWidth;
207 std::optional<LayoutUnit> m_overridingHeight;
208};

210void RenderFlexibleBox::computeChildIntrinsicLogicalWidths(RenderObject& childObject, LayoutUnit& minPreferredLogicalWidth, LayoutUnit& maxPreferredLogicalWidth) const
211{
212 ASSERT(childObject.isBox());
213 RenderBox& child = downcast<RenderBox>(childObject);
214
215 // If the item cross size should use the definite container cross size then set the overriding size now so
216 // the intrinsic sizes are properly computed in the presence of aspect ratios. The only exception is when
217 // we are both a flex item&container, because our parent might have already set our overriding size.
218 if (childCrossSizeShouldUseContainerCrossSize(child) && !isFlexItem()) {
219 auto axis = mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis(child) ? OverridingSizesScope::Axis::Block : OverridingSizesScope::Axis::Inline;
220 OverridingSizesScope overridingSizeScope(child, axis, computeCrossSizeForChildUsingContainerCrossSize(child));
221 RenderBlock::computeChildIntrinsicLogicalWidths(childObject, minPreferredLogicalWidth, maxPreferredLogicalWidth);
222 return;
223 }
224
225 OverridingSizesScope cleanOverridingSizesScope(child, OverridingSizesScope::Axis::Both);
226 RenderBlock::computeChildIntrinsicLogicalWidths(childObject, minPreferredLogicalWidth, maxPreferredLogicalWidth);
227}

229LayoutUnit RenderFlexibleBox::baselinePosition(FontBaseline, bool, LineDirectionMode direction, LinePositionMode) const
230{
231 auto baseline = firstLineBaseline();
232 if (!baseline)
233 return synthesizedBaselineFromBorderBox(*this, direction) + marginLogicalHeight();
234
235 return baseline.value() + (direction == HorizontalLine ? marginTop() : marginRight()).toInt();
236}
237
238std::optional<LayoutUnit> RenderFlexibleBox::firstLineBaseline() const
239{
240 if (isWritingModeRoot() || m_numberOfInFlowChildrenOnFirstLine <= 0 || shouldApplyLayoutContainment(*this))
241 return std::optional<LayoutUnit>();
242 RenderBox* baselineChild = nullptr;
243 int childNumber = 0;
244 for (RenderBox* child = m_orderIterator.first(); child; child = m_orderIterator.next()) {
245 if (m_orderIterator.shouldSkipChild(*child))
246 continue;
247 if (alignmentForChild(*child) == ItemPosition::Baseline && !hasAutoMarginsInCrossAxis(*child)) {
248 baselineChild = child;
249 break;
250 }
251 if (!baselineChild)
252 baselineChild = child;
253
254 ++childNumber;
255 if (childNumber == m_numberOfInFlowChildrenOnFirstLine)
256 break;
257 }
258
259 if (!baselineChild)
260 return std::optional<LayoutUnit>();
261
262 if (!isColumnFlow() && !mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis(*baselineChild))
263 return LayoutUnit { (crossAxisExtentForChild(*baselineChild) + baselineChild->logicalTop()).toInt() };
264 if (isColumnFlow() && mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis(*baselineChild))
265 return LayoutUnit { (mainAxisExtentForChild(*baselineChild) + baselineChild->logicalTop()).toInt() };
266
267 std::optional<LayoutUnit> baseline = baselineChild->firstLineBaseline();
268 if (!baseline) {
269 // FIXME: We should pass |direction| into firstLineBoxBaseline and stop bailing out if we're a writing mode root.
270 // This would also fix some cases where the flexbox is orthogonal to its container.
271 LineDirectionMode direction = isHorizontalWritingMode() ? HorizontalLine : VerticalLine;
272 return synthesizedBaselineFromBorderBox(*baselineChild, direction) + baselineChild->logicalTop();
273 }
274
275 return LayoutUnit { (baseline.value() + baselineChild->logicalTop()).toInt() };
276}
277
278std::optional<LayoutUnit> RenderFlexibleBox::inlineBlockBaseline(LineDirectionMode) const
279{
280 return firstLineBaseline();
281}

283static const StyleContentAlignmentData& contentAlignmentNormalBehavior()
284{
285 // The justify-content property applies along the main axis, but since
286 // flexing in the main axis is controlled by flex, stretch behaves as
287 // flex-start (ignoring the specified fallback alignment, if any).
288 // https://drafts.csswg.org/css-align/#distribution-flex
289 static const StyleContentAlignmentData normalBehavior = { ContentPosition::Normal, ContentDistribution::Stretch};
290 return normalBehavior;
291}
292
293void RenderFlexibleBox::styleDidChange(StyleDifference diff, const RenderStyle* oldStyle)
294{
295 RenderBlock::styleDidChange(diff, oldStyle);
296 if (!oldStyle || diff != StyleDifference::Layout)
297 return;
298
299 if (oldStyle->resolvedAlignItems(selfAlignmentNormalBehavior()).position() == ItemPosition::Stretch) {
300 // Flex items that were previously stretching need to be relayed out so we
301 // can compute new available cross axis space. This is only necessary for
302 // stretching since other alignment values don't change the size of the
303 // box.
304 for (auto& child : childrenOfType<RenderBox>(*this)) {
305 ItemPosition previousAlignment = child.style().resolvedAlignSelf(oldStyle, selfAlignmentNormalBehavior()).position();
306 if (previousAlignment == ItemPosition::Stretch && previousAlignment != child.style().resolvedAlignSelf(&style(), selfAlignmentNormalBehavior()).position())
307 child.setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
308 }
309 }
310}

312bool RenderFlexibleBox::hitTestChildren(const HitTestRequest& request, HitTestResult& result, const HitTestLocation& locationInContainer, const LayoutPoint& adjustedLocation, HitTestAction hitTestAction)
313{
314 if (hitTestAction != HitTestForeground)
315 return false;
316
317 LayoutPoint scrolledOffset = hasOverflowClip() ? adjustedLocation - toLayoutSize(scrollPosition()) : adjustedLocation;
318
319 // If collecting the children in reverse order is bad for performance, this Vector could be determined at layout time.
320 Vector<RenderBox*> reversedOrderIteratorForHitTesting;
321 for (auto* child = m_orderIterator.first(); child; child = m_orderIterator.next()) {
322 if (m_orderIterator.shouldSkipChild(*child))
323 continue;
324 reversedOrderIteratorForHitTesting.append(child);
325 }
326 reversedOrderIteratorForHitTesting.reverse();
327
328 for (auto* child : reversedOrderIteratorForHitTesting) {
329 if (child->hasSelfPaintingLayer())
330 continue;
331 auto childPoint = flipForWritingModeForChild(child, scrolledOffset);
332 if (child->hitTest(request, result, locationInContainer, childPoint)) {
333 updateHitTestResult(result, flipForWritingMode(toLayoutPoint(locationInContainer.point() - adjustedLocation)));
334 return true;
335 }
336 }
337
338 return false;
339}

341void RenderFlexibleBox::layoutBlock(bool relayoutChildren, LayoutUnit)
342{
343 ASSERT(needsLayout());
344
345 if (!relayoutChildren && simplifiedLayout())
346 return;
347
348 LayoutRepainter repainter(*this, checkForRepaintDuringLayout());
349
350 resetLogicalHeightBeforeLayoutIfNeeded();
351 m_relaidOutChildren.clear();
352
353 bool oldInLayout = m_inLayout;
354 m_inLayout = true;
355
356 if (recomputeLogicalWidth())
357 relayoutChildren = true;
358
359 LayoutUnit previousHeight = logicalHeight();
360 setLogicalHeight(borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight() + scrollbarLogicalHeight());
361 {
362 LayoutStateMaintainer statePusher(*this, locationOffset(), hasTransform() || hasReflection() || style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode());
363
364 preparePaginationBeforeBlockLayout(relayoutChildren);
365
366 m_numberOfInFlowChildrenOnFirstLine = -1;
367
368 beginUpdateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransaction();
369
370 prepareOrderIteratorAndMargins();
371
372 // Fieldsets need to find their legend and position it inside the border of the object.
373 // The legend then gets skipped during normal layout. The same is true for ruby text.
374 // It doesn't get included in the normal layout process but is instead skipped.
375 layoutExcludedChildren(relayoutChildren);
376
377 ChildFrameRects oldChildRects;
378 appendChildFrameRects(oldChildRects);
379
380 layoutFlexItems(relayoutChildren);
381
382 endAndCommitUpdateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransaction();
383
384 if (logicalHeight() != previousHeight)
385 relayoutChildren = true;
386
387 layoutPositionedObjects(relayoutChildren || isDocumentElementRenderer());
388
389 repaintChildrenDuringLayoutIfMoved(oldChildRects);
390 // FIXME: css3/flexbox/repaint-rtl-column.html seems to repaint more overflow than it needs to.
391 computeOverflow(clientLogicalBottomAfterRepositioning());
392 }
393 updateLayerTransform();
394
395 // We have to reset this, because changes to our ancestors' style can affect
396 // this value. Also, this needs to be before we call updateAfterLayout, as
397 // that function may re-enter this one.
398 m_hasDefiniteHeight = SizeDefiniteness::Unknown;
399
400 // Update our scroll information if we're overflow:auto/scroll/hidden now that we know if we overflow or not.
401 updateScrollInfoAfterLayout();
402
403 repainter.repaintAfterLayout();
404
405 clearNeedsLayout();
406
407 m_inLayout = oldInLayout;
408}

410void RenderFlexibleBox::appendChildFrameRects(ChildFrameRects& childFrameRects)
411{
412 for (RenderBox* child = m_orderIterator.first(); child; child = m_orderIterator.next()) {
413 if (!child->isOutOfFlowPositioned())
414 childFrameRects.append(child->frameRect());
415 }
416}
417
418void RenderFlexibleBox::repaintChildrenDuringLayoutIfMoved(const ChildFrameRects& oldChildRects)
419{
420 size_t childIndex = 0;
421 for (RenderBox* child = m_orderIterator.first(); child; child = m_orderIterator.next()) {
422 if (child->isOutOfFlowPositioned())
423 continue;
424
425 // If the child moved, we have to repaint it as well as any floating/positioned
426 // descendants. An exception is if we need a layout. In this case, we know we're going to
427 // repaint ourselves (and the child) anyway.
428 if (!selfNeedsLayout() && child->checkForRepaintDuringLayout())
429 child->repaintDuringLayoutIfMoved(oldChildRects[childIndex]);
430 ++childIndex;
431 }
432 ASSERT(childIndex == oldChildRects.size());
433}

435void RenderFlexibleBox::paintChildren(PaintInfo& paintInfo, const LayoutPoint& paintOffset, PaintInfo& paintInfoForChild, bool usePrintRect)
436{
437 for (RenderBox* child = m_orderIterator.first(); child; child = m_orderIterator.next()) {
438 if (!paintChild(*child, paintInfo, paintOffset, paintInfoForChild, usePrintRect, PaintAsInlineBlock))
439 return;
440 }
441}

443void RenderFlexibleBox::repositionLogicalHeightDependentFlexItems(Vector<LineContext>& lineContexts, LayoutUnit gapBetweenLines)
444{
445 LayoutUnit crossAxisStartEdge = lineContexts.isEmpty() ? 0_lu : lineContexts[0].crossAxisOffset;
446 // If we have a single line flexbox, the line height is all the available space. For flex-direction: row,
447 // this means we need to use the height, so we do this after calling updateLogicalHeight.
448 if (!isMultiline() && !lineContexts.isEmpty())
449 lineContexts[0].crossAxisExtent = crossAxisContentExtent();
450
451 alignFlexLines(lineContexts, gapBetweenLines);
452
453 alignChildren(lineContexts);
454
455 if (style().flexWrap() == FlexWrap::Reverse)
456 flipForWrapReverse(lineContexts, crossAxisStartEdge);
457
458 // direction:rtl + flex-direction:column means the cross-axis direction is
459 // flipped.
460 flipForRightToLeftColumn(lineContexts);
461}
462
463LayoutUnit RenderFlexibleBox::clientLogicalBottomAfterRepositioning()
464{
465 LayoutUnit maxChildLogicalBottom;
466 for (RenderBox* child = firstChildBox(); child; child = child->nextSiblingBox()) {
467 if (child->isOutOfFlowPositioned())
468 continue;
469 LayoutUnit childLogicalBottom = logicalTopForChild(*child) + logicalHeightForChild(*child) + marginAfterForChild(*child);
470 maxChildLogicalBottom = std::max(maxChildLogicalBottom, childLogicalBottom);
471 }
472 return std::max(clientLogicalBottom(), maxChildLogicalBottom + paddingAfter());
473}

475bool RenderFlexibleBox::mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis(const RenderBox& child) const
476{
477 return isHorizontalFlow() == child.isHorizontalWritingMode();
478}
479
480bool RenderFlexibleBox::isColumnFlow() const
481{
482 return style().isColumnFlexDirection();
483}
484
485bool RenderFlexibleBox::isHorizontalFlow() const
486{
487 if (isHorizontalWritingMode())
488 return !isColumnFlow();
489 return isColumnFlow();
490}
491
492bool RenderFlexibleBox::isLeftToRightFlow() const
493{
494 if (isColumnFlow())
495 return style().writingMode() == WritingMode::TopToBottom || style().writingMode() == WritingMode::LeftToRight;
496 return style().isLeftToRightDirection() ^ (style().flexDirection() == FlexDirection::RowReverse);
497}

499bool RenderFlexibleBox::isMultiline() const
500{
501 return style().flexWrap() != FlexWrap::NoWrap;
502}

504// https://drafts.csswg.org/css-flexbox/#min-size-auto
505bool RenderFlexibleBox::shouldApplyMinSizeAutoForChild(const RenderBox& child) const
506{
507 auto minSize = mainSizeLengthForChild(MinSize, child);
508 // min, max and fit-content are equivalent to the automatic size for block sizes https://drafts.csswg.org/css-sizing-3/#valdef-width-min-content.
509 bool childBlockSizeIsEquivalentToAutomaticSize = !mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis(child) && (minSize.isMinContent() || minSize.isMaxContent() || minSize.isFitContent());
510
511 return (minSize.isAuto() || childBlockSizeIsEquivalentToAutomaticSize) && (mainAxisOverflowForChild(child) == Overflow::Visible);
512}

514Length RenderFlexibleBox::flexBasisForChild(const RenderBox& child) const
515{
516 Length flexLength = child.style().flexBasis();
517 if (flexLength.isAuto())
518 flexLength = mainSizeLengthForChild(MainOrPreferredSize, child);
519 return flexLength;
520}

527LayoutUnit RenderFlexibleBox::cachedChildIntrinsicContentLogicalHeight(const RenderBox& child) const
528{
529 if (child.isRenderReplaced())
530 return downcast<RenderReplaced>(child).intrinsicLogicalHeight();
531
532 if (m_intrinsicContentLogicalHeights.contains(&child))
533 return m_intrinsicContentLogicalHeights.get(&child);
534
535 return child.contentLogicalHeight();
536}
537
538void RenderFlexibleBox::setCachedChildIntrinsicContentLogicalHeight(const RenderBox& child, LayoutUnit height)
539{
540 if (child.isRenderReplaced())
541 return; // Replaced elements know their intrinsic height already, so save space by not caching.
542 m_intrinsicContentLogicalHeights.set(&child, height);
543}
544
545void RenderFlexibleBox::clearCachedChildIntrinsicContentLogicalHeight(const RenderBox& child)
546{
547 if (child.isRenderReplaced())
548 return; // Replaced elements know their intrinsic height already, so nothing to do.
549 m_intrinsicContentLogicalHeights.remove(&child);
550}
551
552LayoutUnit RenderFlexibleBox::childIntrinsicLogicalHeight(RenderBox& child) const
553{
554 // This should only be called if the logical height is the cross size
555 ASSERT(mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis(child));
556 if (needToStretchChildLogicalHeight(child)) {
557 LayoutUnit childContentHeight = cachedChildIntrinsicContentLogicalHeight(child);
558 LayoutUnit childLogicalHeight = childContentHeight + child.scrollbarLogicalHeight() + child.borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight();
559 return child.constrainLogicalHeightByMinMax(childLogicalHeight, childContentHeight);
560 }
561 return child.logicalHeight();
562}
563
564LayoutUnit RenderFlexibleBox::childIntrinsicLogicalWidth(RenderBox& child)
565{
566 // This should only be called if the logical width is the cross size
567 ASSERT(!mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis(child));
568 if (childCrossSizeIsDefinite(child, child.style().logicalWidth()))
569 return child.logicalWidth();
570
571 LogicalExtentComputedValues values;
572 {
573 OverridingSizesScope cleanOverridingWidthScope(child, OverridingSizesScope::Axis::Inline);
574 child.computeLogicalWidthInFragment(values);
575 }
576 return values.m_extent;
577}
578
579LayoutUnit RenderFlexibleBox::crossAxisIntrinsicExtentForChild(RenderBox& child)
580{
581 return mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis(child) ? childIntrinsicLogicalHeight(child) : childIntrinsicLogicalWidth(child);
582}
583
584LayoutUnit RenderFlexibleBox::mainAxisExtentForChild(const RenderBox& child) const
585{
586 return isHorizontalFlow() ? child.size().width() : child.size().height();
587}
588
589LayoutUnit RenderFlexibleBox::mainAxisContentExtentForChildIncludingScrollbar(const RenderBox& child) const
590{
591 return isHorizontalFlow() ? child.contentWidth() + child.verticalScrollbarWidth() : child.contentHeight() + child.horizontalScrollbarHeight();
592}
593
594LayoutUnit RenderFlexibleBox::crossAxisExtent() const
595{
596 return isHorizontalFlow() ? size().height() : size().width();
597}
598
599LayoutUnit RenderFlexibleBox::mainAxisExtent() const
600{
601 return isHorizontalFlow() ? size().width() : size().height();
602}
603
604LayoutUnit RenderFlexibleBox::crossAxisContentExtent() const
605{
606 return isHorizontalFlow() ? contentHeight() : contentWidth();
607}
608
609LayoutUnit RenderFlexibleBox::mainAxisContentExtent(LayoutUnit contentLogicalHeight)
610{
611 if (!isColumnFlow())
612 return contentLogicalWidth();
613
614 LayoutUnit borderPaddingAndScrollbar = borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight() + scrollbarLogicalHeight();
615 LayoutUnit borderBoxLogicalHeight = contentLogicalHeight + borderPaddingAndScrollbar;
616 auto computedValues = computeLogicalHeight(borderBoxLogicalHeight, logicalTop());
617 if (computedValues.m_extent == LayoutUnit::max())
618 return computedValues.m_extent;
619 return std::max(0_lu, computedValues.m_extent - borderPaddingAndScrollbar);
620}

622static bool childHasAspectRatio(const RenderBox& child)
623{
624 return child.hasIntrinsicAspectRatio() || child.style().hasAspectRatio();
625}
626
627std::optional<LayoutUnit> RenderFlexibleBox::computeMainAxisExtentForChild(RenderBox& child, SizeType sizeType, const Length& size)
628{
629 // If we have a horizontal flow, that means the main size is the width.
630 // That's the logical width for horizontal writing modes, and the logical
631 // height in vertical writing modes. For a vertical flow, main size is the
632 // height, so it's the inverse. So we need the logical width if we have a
633 // horizontal flow and horizontal writing mode, or vertical flow and vertical
634 // writing mode. Otherwise we need the logical height.
635 if (!mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis(child)) {
636 // We don't have to check for "auto" here - computeContentLogicalHeight
637 // will just return a null Optional for that case anyway. It's safe to access
638 // scrollbarLogicalHeight here because ComputeNextFlexLine will have
639 // already forced layout on the child. We previously did a layout out the child
640 // if necessary (see ComputeNextFlexLine and the call to
641 // childHasIntrinsicMainAxisSize) so we can be sure that the two height
642 // calls here will return up-to-date data.
643 std::optional<LayoutUnit> height = child.computeContentLogicalHeight(sizeType, size, cachedChildIntrinsicContentLogicalHeight(child));
644 if (!height)
645 return height;
646 return height.value() + child.scrollbarLogicalHeight();
647 }
648
649 // computeLogicalWidth always re-computes the intrinsic widths. However, when
650 // our logical width is auto, we can just use our cached value. So let's do
651 // that here. (Compare code in RenderBlock::computePreferredLogicalWidths)
652 if (child.style().logicalWidth().isAuto() && !childHasAspectRatio(child)) {
653 if (size.isMinContent()) {
654 if (child.needsPreferredWidthsRecalculation())
655 child.setPreferredLogicalWidthsDirty(true, MarkOnlyThis);
656 return child.minPreferredLogicalWidth() - child.borderAndPaddingLogicalWidth();
657 }
658 if (size.isMaxContent()) {
659 if (child.needsPreferredWidthsRecalculation())
660 child.setPreferredLogicalWidthsDirty(true, MarkOnlyThis);
661 return child.maxPreferredLogicalWidth() - child.borderAndPaddingLogicalWidth();
662 }
663 }
664
665 // FIXME: Figure out how this should work for regions and pass in the appropriate values.
666 RenderFragmentContainer* fragment = nullptr;
667 return child.computeLogicalWidthInFragmentUsing(sizeType, size, contentLogicalWidth(), *this, fragment) - child.borderAndPaddingLogicalWidth();
668}
669
670WritingMode RenderFlexibleBox::transformedWritingMode() const
671{
672 WritingMode mode = style().writingMode();
673 if (!isColumnFlow())
674 return mode;
675
676 switch (mode) {
677 case WritingMode::TopToBottom:
678 case WritingMode::BottomToTop:
679 return style().isLeftToRightDirection() ? WritingMode::LeftToRight : WritingMode::RightToLeft;
680 case WritingMode::LeftToRight:
681 case WritingMode::RightToLeft:
682 return style().isLeftToRightDirection() ? WritingMode::TopToBottom : WritingMode::BottomToTop;
683 }
684 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
685 return WritingMode::TopToBottom;
686}

862// FIXME: computeMainSizeFromAspectRatioUsing may need to return an std::optional<LayoutUnit> in the future
863// rather than returning indefinite sizes as 0/-1.
864LayoutUnit RenderFlexibleBox::computeMainSizeFromAspectRatioUsing(const RenderBox& child, Length crossSizeLength) const
865{
866 ASSERT(childHasAspectRatio(child));
867
868 auto adjustForBoxSizing = [this] (const RenderBox& box, Length length) -> LayoutUnit {
869 ASSERT(length.isFixed());
870 auto value = LayoutUnit(length.value());
871 // We need to substract the border and padding extent from the cross axis.
872 // Furthermore, the sizing calculations that floor the content box size at zero when applying box-sizing are also ignored.
873 // https://drafts.csswg.org/css-flexbox/#algo-main-item.
874 if (box.style().boxSizing() == BoxSizing::BorderBox)
875 value -= isHorizontalFlow() ? box.verticalBorderAndPaddingExtent() : box.horizontalBorderAndPaddingExtent();
876 return value;
877 };
878
879 std::optional<LayoutUnit> crossSize;
880 if (crossSizeLength.isFixed())
881 crossSize = adjustForBoxSizing(child, crossSizeLength);
882 else if (crossSizeLength.isAuto())
883 crossSize = computeCrossSizeForChildUsingContainerCrossSize(child);
884 else {
885 ASSERT(crossSizeLength.isPercentOrCalculated());
886 crossSize = mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis(child) ? child.computePercentageLogicalHeight(crossSizeLength) : adjustBorderBoxLogicalWidthForBoxSizing(valueForLength(crossSizeLength, contentWidth()), crossSizeLength.type());
887 if (!crossSize)
888 return 0_lu;
889 }
890
891 const LayoutSize& childIntrinsicSize = child.intrinsicSize();
892 double ratio;
893 if (child.style().aspectRatioType() == AspectRatioType::Ratio || (child.style().aspectRatioType() == AspectRatioType::AutoAndRatio && childIntrinsicSize.isEmpty()))
894 ratio = child.style().aspectRatioWidth() / child.style().aspectRatioHeight();
895 else {
896 ASSERT(childIntrinsicSize.height());
897 ratio = childIntrinsicSize.width().toFloat() / childIntrinsicSize.height().toFloat();
898 }
899 if (isHorizontalFlow())
900 return LayoutUnit(crossSize.value() * ratio);
901 return LayoutUnit(crossSize.value() / ratio);
902}

905{
906 if (isHorizontalFlow())
907 child.setLocation(location);
908 else
909 child.setLocation(location.transposedPoint());
910}

912bool RenderFlexibleBox::canComputePercentageFlexBasis(const RenderBox& child, const Length& flexBasis, UpdatePercentageHeightDescendants updateDescendants)
913{
914 if (!isColumnFlow() || m_hasDefiniteHeight == SizeDefiniteness::Definite)
915 return true;
916 if (m_hasDefiniteHeight == SizeDefiniteness::Indefinite)
917 return false;
918 bool definite = child.computePercentageLogicalHeight(flexBasis, updateDescendants).has_value();
919 if (m_inLayout && (isHorizontalWritingMode() == child.isHorizontalWritingMode())) {
920 // We can reach this code even while we're not laying ourselves out, such
921 // as from mainSizeForPercentageResolution.
922 m_hasDefiniteHeight = definite ? SizeDefiniteness::Definite : SizeDefiniteness::Indefinite;
923 }
924 return definite;
925}
926
927bool RenderFlexibleBox::childMainSizeIsDefinite(const RenderBox& child, const Length& flexBasis)
928{
929 if (flexBasis.isAuto())
930 return false;
931 if (isColumnFlow() && (flexBasis.isIntrinsic() || flexBasis.type() == LengthType::Intrinsic))
932 return false;
933 if (flexBasis.isPercentOrCalculated())
934 return canComputePercentageFlexBasis(child, flexBasis, UpdatePercentageHeightDescendants::No);
935 return true;
936}

938bool RenderFlexibleBox::childHasComputableAspectRatio(const RenderBox& child) const
939{
940 if (!childHasAspectRatio(child))
941 return false;
942 return child.intrinsicSize().height() || child.style().hasAspectRatio();
943}
944
945bool RenderFlexibleBox::childHasComputableAspectRatioAndCrossSizeIsConsideredDefinite(const RenderBox& child)
946{
947 return childHasComputableAspectRatio(child)
948 && (childCrossSizeIsDefinite(child, crossSizeLengthForChild(MainOrPreferredSize, child)) || childCrossSizeShouldUseContainerCrossSize(child));
949}
950
951bool RenderFlexibleBox::childCrossSizeShouldUseContainerCrossSize(const RenderBox& child) const
952{
953 // 9.8 https://drafts.csswg.org/css-flexbox/#definite-sizes
954 // 1. If a single-line flex container has a definite cross size, the automatic preferred outer cross size of any
955 // stretched flex items is the flex container's inner cross size (clamped to the flex item's min and max cross size)
956 // and is considered definite.
957 if (!isMultiline() && alignmentForChild(child) == ItemPosition::Stretch && !hasAutoMarginsInCrossAxis(child) && crossSizeLengthForChild(MainOrPreferredSize, child).isAuto()) {
958 // This must be kept in sync with computeMainSizeFromAspectRatioUsing().
959 // FIXME: so far we're only considered fixed sizes but we should extend it to other definite sizes.
960 auto& crossSize = isHorizontalFlow() ? style().height() : style().width();
961 return crossSize.isFixed();
962 }
963 return false;
964}
965
966bool RenderFlexibleBox::childCrossSizeIsDefinite(const RenderBox& child, const Length& length)
967{
968 if (length.isAuto())
969 return false;
970
971 if (length.isPercentOrCalculated()) {
972 if (!mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis(child) || m_hasDefiniteHeight == SizeDefiniteness::Definite)
973 return true;
974 if (m_hasDefiniteHeight == SizeDefiniteness::Indefinite)
975 return false;
976 bool definite = bool(child.computePercentageLogicalHeight(length));
977 m_hasDefiniteHeight = definite ? SizeDefiniteness::Definite : SizeDefiniteness::Indefinite;
978 return definite;
979 }
980 // FIXME: Eventually we should support other types of sizes here.
981 // Requires updating computeMainSizeFromAspectRatioUsing.
982 return length.isFixed();
983}
984
985void RenderFlexibleBox::cacheChildMainSize(const RenderBox& child)
986{
987 ASSERT(!child.needsLayout());
988 LayoutUnit mainSize;
989 if (mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis(child))
990 mainSize = child.maxPreferredLogicalWidth();
991 else {
992 auto flexBasis = flexBasisForChild(child);
993 if (flexBasis.isPercentOrCalculated() && !childMainSizeIsDefinite(child, flexBasis))
994 mainSize = cachedChildIntrinsicContentLogicalHeight(child) + child.borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight() + child.scrollbarLogicalHeight();
995 else
996 mainSize = child.logicalHeight();
997 }
998
999 m_intrinsicSizeAlongMainAxis.set(&child, mainSize);
1000 m_relaidOutChildren.add(&child);
1001}
1002
1003void RenderFlexibleBox::clearCachedMainSizeForChild(const RenderBox& child)
1004{
1005 m_intrinsicSizeAlongMainAxis.remove(&child);
1006}
1007
1008LayoutUnit RenderFlexibleBox::computeInnerFlexBaseSizeForChild(RenderBox& child, LayoutUnit mainAxisBorderAndPadding)
1009{
1010 Length flexBasis = flexBasisForChild(child);
1011 if (childMainSizeIsDefinite(child, flexBasis))
1012 return std::max(0_lu, computeMainAxisExtentForChild(child, MainOrPreferredSize, flexBasis).value());
1013
1014 if (childHasComputableAspectRatioAndCrossSizeIsConsideredDefinite(child)) {
1015 const Length& crossSizeLength = crossSizeLengthForChild(MainOrPreferredSize, child);
1016 return adjustChildSizeForAspectRatioCrossAxisMinAndMax(child, computeMainSizeFromAspectRatioUsing(child, crossSizeLength));
1017 }
1018
1019 // The flex basis is indefinite (=auto), so we need to compute the actual width of the child.
1020 LayoutUnit mainAxisExtent;
1021 if (!mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis(child)) {
1022 ASSERT(!child.needsLayout());
1023 ASSERT(m_intrinsicSizeAlongMainAxis.contains(&child));
1024 mainAxisExtent = m_intrinsicSizeAlongMainAxis.get(&child);
1025 } else {
1026 // We don't need to add scrollbarLogicalWidth here because the preferred
1027 // width includes the scrollbar, even for overflow: auto.
1028 mainAxisExtent = child.maxPreferredLogicalWidth();
1029 }
1030 return mainAxisExtent - mainAxisBorderAndPadding;
1031}
1032
1033void RenderFlexibleBox::layoutFlexItems(bool relayoutChildren)
1034{
1035 Vector<LineContext> lineContexts;
1036 LayoutUnit sumFlexBaseSize;
1037 double totalFlexGrow;
1038 double totalFlexShrink;
1039 double totalWeightedFlexShrink;
1040 LayoutUnit sumHypotheticalMainSize;
1041
1042 // Set up our master list of flex items. All of the rest of the algorithm
1043 // should work off this list of a subset.
1044 // TODO(cbiesinger): That second part is not yet true.
1045 Vector<FlexItem> allItems;
1046 m_orderIterator.first();
1047 for (RenderBox* child = m_orderIterator.currentChild(); child; child = m_orderIterator.next()) {
1048 if (m_orderIterator.shouldSkipChild(*child)) {
1049 // Out-of-flow children are not flex items, so we skip them here.
1050 if (child->isOutOfFlowPositioned())
1051 prepareChildForPositionedLayout(*child);
1052 continue;
1053 }
1054 allItems.append(constructFlexItem(*child, relayoutChildren));
1055 // constructFlexItem() might set the override containing block height so any value cached for definiteness might be incorrect.
1056 m_hasDefiniteHeight = SizeDefiniteness::Unknown;
1057 }
1058
1059 const LayoutUnit lineBreakLength = mainAxisContentExtent(LayoutUnit::max());
1060 LayoutUnit gapBetweenItems = computeGap(GapType::BetweenItems);
1061 LayoutUnit gapBetweenLines = computeGap(GapType::BetweenLines);
1062 FlexLayoutAlgorithm flexAlgorithm(style(), lineBreakLength, allItems, gapBetweenItems, gapBetweenLines);
1063 LayoutUnit crossAxisOffset = flowAwareBorderBefore() + flowAwarePaddingBefore();
1064 Vector<FlexItem> lineItems;
1065 size_t nextIndex = 0;
1066 size_t numLines = 0;
1067 while (flexAlgorithm.computeNextFlexLine(nextIndex, lineItems, sumFlexBaseSize, totalFlexGrow, totalFlexShrink, totalWeightedFlexShrink, sumHypotheticalMainSize)) {
1068 ++numLines;
1069 LayoutUnit containerMainInnerSize = mainAxisContentExtent(sumHypotheticalMainSize);
1070 // availableFreeSpace is the initial amount of free space in this flexbox.
1071 // remainingFreeSpace starts out at the same value but as we place and lay
1072 // out flex items we subtract from it. Note that both values can be
1073 // negative.
1074 LayoutUnit remainingFreeSpace = containerMainInnerSize - sumFlexBaseSize;
1075 FlexSign flexSign = (sumHypotheticalMainSize < containerMainInnerSize) ? PositiveFlexibility : NegativeFlexibility;
1076 freezeInflexibleItems(flexSign, lineItems, remainingFreeSpace, totalFlexGrow, totalFlexShrink, totalWeightedFlexShrink);
1077 // The initial free space gets calculated after freezing inflexible items.
1078 // https://drafts.csswg.org/css-flexbox/#resolve-flexible-lengths step 3
1079 const LayoutUnit initialFreeSpace = remainingFreeSpace;
1080 while (!resolveFlexibleLengths(flexSign, lineItems, initialFreeSpace, remainingFreeSpace, totalFlexGrow, totalFlexShrink, totalWeightedFlexShrink)) {
1081 ASSERT(totalFlexGrow >= 0);
1082 ASSERT(totalWeightedFlexShrink >= 0);
1083 }
1084
1085 // Recalculate the remaining free space. The adjustment for flex factors
1086 // between 0..1 means we can't just use remainingFreeSpace here.
1087 remainingFreeSpace = containerMainInnerSize;
1088 for (size_t i = 0; i < lineItems.size(); ++i) {
1089 FlexItem& flexItem = lineItems[i];
1090 ASSERT(!flexItem.box.isOutOfFlowPositioned());
1091 remainingFreeSpace -= flexItem.flexedMarginBoxSize();
1092 }
1093 remainingFreeSpace -= (lineItems.size() - 1) * gapBetweenItems;
1094
1095 // This will std::move lineItems into a newly-created LineContext.
1096 layoutAndPlaceChildren(crossAxisOffset, lineItems, remainingFreeSpace, relayoutChildren, lineContexts, gapBetweenItems);
1097 }
1098
1099 if (hasLineIfEmpty()) {
1100 // Even if computeNextFlexLine returns true, the flexbox might not have
1101 // a line because all our children might be out of flow positioned.
1102 // Instead of just checking if we have a line, make sure the flexbox
1103 // has at least a line's worth of height to cover this case.
1104 LayoutUnit minHeight = borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight() + lineHeight(true, isHorizontalWritingMode() ? HorizontalLine : VerticalLine, PositionOfInteriorLineBoxes) + scrollbarLogicalHeight();
1105 if (size().height() < minHeight)
1106 setLogicalHeight(minHeight);
1107 }
1108
1109 if (!isColumnFlow() && numLines > 1)
1110 setLogicalHeight(logicalHeight() + computeGap(GapType::BetweenLines) * (numLines - 1));
1111
1112 updateLogicalHeight();
1113 repositionLogicalHeightDependentFlexItems(lineContexts, gapBetweenLines);
1114}
1115
1116LayoutUnit RenderFlexibleBox::autoMarginOffsetInMainAxis(const Vector<FlexItem>& children, LayoutUnit& availableFreeSpace)
1117{
1118 if (availableFreeSpace <= 0_lu)
1119 return 0_lu;
1120
1121 int numberOfAutoMargins = 0;
1122 bool isHorizontal = isHorizontalFlow();
1123 for (size_t i = 0; i < children.size(); ++i) {
1124 const auto& child = children[i].box;
1125 ASSERT(!child.isOutOfFlowPositioned());
1126 if (isHorizontal) {
1127 if (child.style().marginLeft().isAuto())
1128 ++numberOfAutoMargins;
1129 if (child.style().marginRight().isAuto())
1130 ++numberOfAutoMargins;
1131 } else {
1132 if (child.style().marginTop().isAuto())
1133 ++numberOfAutoMargins;
1134 if (child.style().marginBottom().isAuto())
1135 ++numberOfAutoMargins;
1136 }
1137 }
1138 if (!numberOfAutoMargins)
1139 return 0_lu;
1140
1141 LayoutUnit sizeOfAutoMargin = availableFreeSpace / numberOfAutoMargins;
1142 availableFreeSpace = 0_lu;
1143 return sizeOfAutoMargin;
1144}
1145
1146void RenderFlexibleBox::updateAutoMarginsInMainAxis(RenderBox& child, LayoutUnit autoMarginOffset)
1147{
1148 ASSERT(autoMarginOffset >= 0_lu);
1149
1150 if (isHorizontalFlow()) {
1151 if (child.style().marginLeft().isAuto())
1152 child.setMarginLeft(autoMarginOffset);
1153 if (child.style().marginRight().isAuto())
1154 child.setMarginRight(autoMarginOffset);
1155 } else {
1156 if (child.style().marginTop().isAuto())
1157 child.setMarginTop(autoMarginOffset);
1158 if (child.style().marginBottom().isAuto())
1159 child.setMarginBottom(autoMarginOffset);
1160 }
1161}

1165 if (isHorizontalFlow())
1166 return child.style().marginTop().isAuto() || child.style().marginBottom().isAuto();
1167 return child.style().marginLeft().isAuto() || child.style().marginRight().isAuto();
1168}

1170LayoutUnit RenderFlexibleBox::availableAlignmentSpaceForChild(LayoutUnit lineCrossAxisExtent, const RenderBox& child)
1171{
1172 ASSERT(!child.isOutOfFlowPositioned());
1173 LayoutUnit childCrossExtent = crossAxisMarginExtentForChild(child) + crossAxisExtentForChild(child);
1174 return lineCrossAxisExtent - childCrossExtent;

1176
1177bool RenderFlexibleBox::updateAutoMarginsInCrossAxis(RenderBox& child, LayoutUnit availableAlignmentSpace)
1178{
1179 ASSERT(!child.isOutOfFlowPositioned());
1180 ASSERT(availableAlignmentSpace >= 0_lu);
1181
1182 bool isHorizontal = isHorizontalFlow();
1183 Length topOrLeft = isHorizontal ? child.style().marginTop() : child.style().marginLeft();
1184 Length bottomOrRight = isHorizontal ? child.style().marginBottom() : child.style().marginRight();
1185 if (topOrLeft.isAuto() && bottomOrRight.isAuto()) {
1186 adjustAlignmentForChild(child, availableAlignmentSpace / 2);
1187 if (isHorizontal) {
1188 child.setMarginTop(availableAlignmentSpace / 2);
1189 child.setMarginBottom(availableAlignmentSpace / 2);
1190 } else {
1191 child.setMarginLeft(availableAlignmentSpace / 2);
1192 child.setMarginRight(availableAlignmentSpace / 2);
1193 }
1194 return true;
1195 }
1196 bool shouldAdjustTopOrLeft = true;
1197 if (isColumnFlow() && !child.style().isLeftToRightDirection()) {
1198 // For column flows, only make this adjustment if topOrLeft corresponds to
1199 // the "before" margin, so that flipForRightToLeftColumn will do the right
1200 // thing.
1201 shouldAdjustTopOrLeft = false;
1202 }
1203 if (!isColumnFlow() && child.style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode()) {
1204 // If we are a flipped writing mode, we need to adjust the opposite side.
1205 // This is only needed for row flows because this only affects the
1206 // block-direction axis.
1207 shouldAdjustTopOrLeft = false;
1208 }
1209
1210 if (topOrLeft.isAuto()) {
1211 if (shouldAdjustTopOrLeft)
1212 adjustAlignmentForChild(child, availableAlignmentSpace);
1213
1214 if (isHorizontal)
1215 child.setMarginTop(availableAlignmentSpace);
1216 else
1217 child.setMarginLeft(availableAlignmentSpace);
1218 return true;
1219 }
1220
1221 if (bottomOrRight.isAuto()) {
1222 if (!shouldAdjustTopOrLeft)
1223 adjustAlignmentForChild(child, availableAlignmentSpace);
1224
1225 if (isHorizontal)
1226 child.setMarginBottom(availableAlignmentSpace);
1227 else
1228 child.setMarginRight(availableAlignmentSpace);
1229 return true;
1230 }
1231 return false;
1232}
1233
1234LayoutUnit RenderFlexibleBox::marginBoxAscentForChild(const RenderBox& child)
1235{
1236 LayoutUnit ascent = child.firstLineBaseline().value_or(crossAxisExtentForChild(child));
1237 return ascent + flowAwareMarginBeforeForChild(child);
1238}
1239
1240LayoutUnit RenderFlexibleBox::computeChildMarginValue(Length margin)
1241{
1242 // When resolving the margins, we use the content size for resolving percent and calc (for percents in calc expressions) margins.
1243 // Fortunately, percent margins are always computed with respect to the block's width, even for margin-top and margin-bottom.
1244 LayoutUnit availableSize = contentLogicalWidth();
1245 return minimumValueForLength(margin, availableSize);
1246}
1247
1248void RenderFlexibleBox::prepareOrderIteratorAndMargins()
1249{
1250 OrderIteratorPopulator populator(m_orderIterator);
1251
1252 for (RenderBox* child = firstChildBox(); child; child = child->nextSiblingBox()) {
1253 if (!populator.collectChild(*child))
1254 continue;
1255
1256 // Before running the flex algorithm, 'auto' has a margin of 0.
1257 // Also, if we're not auto sizing, we don't do a layout that computes the start/end margins.
1258 if (isHorizontalFlow()) {
1259 child->setMarginLeft(computeChildMarginValue(child->style().marginLeft()));
1260 child->setMarginRight(computeChildMarginValue(child->style().marginRight()));
1261 } else {
1262 child->setMarginTop(computeChildMarginValue(child->style().marginTop()));
1263 child->setMarginBottom(computeChildMarginValue(child->style().marginBottom()));
1264 }
1265 }
1266}
1267
1268std::pair<LayoutUnit, LayoutUnit> RenderFlexibleBox::computeFlexItemMinMaxSizes(RenderBox& child)
1269{
1270 Length max = mainSizeLengthForChild(MaxSize, child);
1271 std::optional<LayoutUnit> maxExtent = std::nullopt;
1272 if (max.isSpecifiedOrIntrinsic())
1273 maxExtent = computeMainAxisExtentForChild(child, MaxSize, max);
1274
1275 Length min = mainSizeLengthForChild(MinSize, child);
1276 // Intrinsic sizes in child's block axis are handled by the min-size:auto code path.
1277 if (min.isSpecified() || (min.isIntrinsic() && mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis(child)))
1278 return { computeMainAxisExtentForChild(child, MinSize, min).value_or(0_lu), maxExtent.value_or(LayoutUnit::max()) };
1279
1280 if (shouldApplyMinSizeAutoForChild(child)) {
1281 // FIXME: If the min value is expected to be valid here, we need to come up with a non optional version of computeMainAxisExtentForChild and
1282 // ensure it's valid through the virtual calls of computeIntrinsicLogicalContentHeightUsing.
1283 LayoutUnit contentSize;
1284 Length childCrossSizeLength = crossSizeLengthForChild(MainOrPreferredSize, child);
1285 if (child.isRenderReplaced() && childHasComputableAspectRatio(child) && childCrossSizeIsDefinite(child, childCrossSizeLength))
1286 contentSize = computeMainSizeFromAspectRatioUsing(child, childCrossSizeLength);
1287 else
1288 contentSize = computeMainAxisExtentForChild(child, MinSize, Length(LengthType::MinContent)).value_or(0);
1289 if (child.hasIntrinsicAspectRatio() && child.intrinsicSize().height())
1290 contentSize = adjustChildSizeForAspectRatioCrossAxisMinAndMax(child, contentSize);
1291 ASSERT(contentSize >= 0);
1292 contentSize = std::min(contentSize, maxExtent.value_or(contentSize));
1293
1294 Length mainSize = mainSizeLengthForChild(MainOrPreferredSize, child);
1295 if (childMainSizeIsDefinite(child, mainSize)) {
1296 LayoutUnit resolvedMainSize = computeMainAxisExtentForChild(child, MainOrPreferredSize, mainSize).value_or(0);
1297 ASSERT(resolvedMainSize >= 0);
1298 LayoutUnit specifiedSize = std::min(resolvedMainSize, maxExtent.value_or(resolvedMainSize));
1299 return { std::min(specifiedSize, contentSize), maxExtent.value_or(LayoutUnit::max()) };
1300 }
1301
1302 if (child.isRenderReplaced() && childHasComputableAspectRatioAndCrossSizeIsConsideredDefinite(child)) {
1303 LayoutUnit transferredSize = computeMainSizeFromAspectRatioUsing(child, childCrossSizeLength);
1304 transferredSize = adjustChildSizeForAspectRatioCrossAxisMinAndMax(child, transferredSize);
1305 return { std::min(transferredSize, contentSize), maxExtent.value_or(LayoutUnit::max()) };
1306 }
1307
1308 return { contentSize, maxExtent.value_or(LayoutUnit::max()) };
1309 }
1310
1311 return { 0_lu, maxExtent.value_or(LayoutUnit::max()) };
1312}
1313
1314bool RenderFlexibleBox::useChildOverridingCrossSizeForPercentageResolution(const RenderBox& child)
1315{
1316 ASSERT(mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis(child));
1317 if (alignmentForChild(child) != ItemPosition::Stretch)
1318 return false;
1319
1320 return child.hasOverridingLogicalHeight();
1321}
1322
1323// This method is only called whenever a descendant of a flex item wants to resolve a percentage in its
1324// block axis (logical height). The key here is that percentages should be generally resolved before the
1325// flex item is flexed, meaning that they shouldn't be recomputed once the flex item has been flexed. There
1326// are some exceptions though that are implemented here, like the case of fully inflexible items with
1327// definite flex-basis, or whenever the flex container has a definite main size. See
1328// https://drafts.csswg.org/css-flexbox/#definite-sizes for additional details.
1329bool RenderFlexibleBox::useChildOverridingMainSizeForPercentageResolution(const RenderBox& child)
1330{
1331 ASSERT(!mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis(child));
1332
1333 // The main size of a fully inflexible item with a definite flex basis is, by definition, definite.
1334 if (child.style().flexGrow() == 0.0 && child.style().flexShrink() == 0.0 && childMainSizeIsDefinite(child, flexBasisForChild(child)))
1335 return child.hasOverridingLogicalHeight();
1336
1337 // This function implements section 9.8. Definite and Indefinite Sizes, case 2) of the flexbox spec.
1338 // If the flex container has a definite main size the flex item post-flexing main size is also treated
1339 // as definite. We make up a percentage to check whether we have a definite size.
1340 if (!canComputePercentageFlexBasis(child, Length(0, LengthType::Percent), UpdatePercentageHeightDescendants::Yes))
1341 return false;
1342
1343 return child.hasOverridingLogicalHeight();
1344}
1345
1346bool RenderFlexibleBox::useChildOverridingLogicalHeightForPercentageResolution(const RenderBox& child)
1347{
1348 if (mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis(child))
1349 return useChildOverridingCrossSizeForPercentageResolution(child);
1350 return useChildOverridingMainSizeForPercentageResolution(child);
1351}
1352
1353LayoutUnit RenderFlexibleBox::adjustChildSizeForAspectRatioCrossAxisMinAndMax(const RenderBox& child, LayoutUnit childSize)
1354{
1355 Length crossMin = crossSizeLengthForChild(MinSize, child);
1356 Length crossMax = crossSizeLengthForChild(MaxSize, child);
1357
1358 if (childCrossSizeIsDefinite(child, crossMax)) {
1359 LayoutUnit maxValue = computeMainSizeFromAspectRatioUsing(child, crossMax);
1360 childSize = std::min(maxValue, childSize);
1361 }
1362
1363 if (childCrossSizeIsDefinite(child, crossMin)) {
1364 LayoutUnit minValue = computeMainSizeFromAspectRatioUsing(child, crossMin);
1365 childSize = std::max(minValue, childSize);
1366 }
1367
1368 return childSize;
1369}
1370
1371// A scoped class that resets either min-width & max-width or min-height & max-height (depending on the
1372// flex container main size) to their initial values on instantiation. It later resets them back to their
1373// original values on destruction. It's used when computing the flex base sizes of flex items as "when determining
1374// the flex base size, the item’s min and max main sizes are ignored (no clamping occurs)". See
1375// https://drafts.csswg.org/css-flexbox/#line-sizing
1376class ScopedUnboundedBox {
1377WTF_MAKE_NONCOPYABLE(ScopedUnboundedBox);
1378public:
1379 ScopedUnboundedBox(RenderBox& box, bool mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis)
1380 : m_box(box)
1381 , m_isHorizontalWritingModeInParallelFlow(mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis == box.isHorizontalWritingMode())
1382 {
1383 m_originalMin = m_isHorizontalWritingModeInParallelFlow ? m_box.style().minWidth() : m_box.style().minHeight();
1384 m_originalMax = m_isHorizontalWritingModeInParallelFlow ? m_box.style().maxWidth() : m_box.style().maxHeight();
1385 if (m_isHorizontalWritingModeInParallelFlow) {
1386 m_box.mutableStyle().setMinWidth(RenderStyle::initialMinSize());
1387 m_box.mutableStyle().setMaxWidth(RenderStyle::initialMaxSize());
1388 return;
1389 }
1390 m_box.mutableStyle().setMinHeight(RenderStyle::initialMinSize());
1391 m_box.mutableStyle().setMaxHeight(RenderStyle::initialMaxSize());
1392 }
1393
1394
1395 ~ScopedUnboundedBox()
1396 {
1397 if (m_isHorizontalWritingModeInParallelFlow) {
1398 m_box.mutableStyle().setMinWidth(WTFMove(m_originalMin));
1399 m_box.mutableStyle().setMaxWidth(WTFMove(m_originalMax));
1400 return;
1401 }
1402 m_box.mutableStyle().setMinHeight(WTFMove(m_originalMin));
1403 m_box.mutableStyle().setMaxHeight(WTFMove(m_originalMax));
1404 }
1405
1406private:
1407 RenderBox& m_box;
1408 bool m_isHorizontalWritingModeInParallelFlow;
1409 Length m_originalMin;
1410 Length m_originalMax;
1411};
1412
1413FlexItem RenderFlexibleBox::constructFlexItem(RenderBox& child, bool relayoutChildren)
1414{
1415 auto childHadLayout = child.everHadLayout();
1416 LayoutUnit borderAndPadding = isHorizontalFlow() ? child.horizontalBorderAndPaddingExtent() : child.verticalBorderAndPaddingExtent();
1417 LayoutUnit childInnerFlexBaseSize;
1418 {
1419 ScopedUnboundedBox unbounded(child, mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis(child));
1420 child.clearOverridingContentSize();
1421 if (childHasIntrinsicMainAxisSize(child)) {
1422 // If this condition is true, then computeMainAxisExtentForChild will call
1423 // child.intrinsicContentLogicalHeight() and child.scrollbarLogicalHeight(),
1424 // so if the child has intrinsic min/max/preferred size, run layout on it now to make sure
1425 // its logical height and scroll bars are up to date.
1426 updateBlockChildDirtyBitsBeforeLayout(relayoutChildren, child);
1427 // Don't resolve percentages in children. This is especially important for the min-height calculation,
1428 // where we want percentages to be treated as auto. For flex-basis itself, this is not a problem because
1429 // by definition we have an indefinite flex basis here and thus percentages should not resolve.
1430 if (child.needsLayout() || !m_intrinsicSizeAlongMainAxis.contains(&child)) {
1431 if (isHorizontalWritingMode() == child.isHorizontalWritingMode())
1432 child.setOverridingContainingBlockContentLogicalHeight(std::nullopt);
1433 else
1434 child.setOverridingContainingBlockContentLogicalWidth(std::nullopt);
1435 child.clearOverridingContentSize();
1436 child.setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
1437 child.layoutIfNeeded();
1438 cacheChildMainSize(child);
1439 child.clearOverridingContainingBlockContentSize();
1440 }
1441 }
1442 childInnerFlexBaseSize = computeInnerFlexBaseSizeForChild(child, borderAndPadding);
1443 }
1444
1445 LayoutUnit margin = isHorizontalFlow() ? child.horizontalMarginExtent() : child.verticalMarginExtent();
1446 return FlexItem(child, childInnerFlexBaseSize, borderAndPadding, margin, computeFlexItemMinMaxSizes(child), childHadLayout);
1447}
1448
1449void RenderFlexibleBox::freezeViolations(Vector<FlexItem*>& violations, LayoutUnit& availableFreeSpace, double& totalFlexGrow, double& totalFlexShrink, double& totalWeightedFlexShrink)
1450{
1451 for (size_t i = 0; i < violations.size(); ++i) {
1452 ASSERT(!violations[i]->frozen);
1453 const auto& child = violations[i]->box;
1454 LayoutUnit childSize = violations[i]->flexedContentSize;
1455 availableFreeSpace -= childSize - violations[i]->flexBaseContentSize;
1456 totalFlexGrow -= child.style().flexGrow();
1457 totalFlexShrink -= child.style().flexShrink();
1458 totalWeightedFlexShrink -= child.style().flexShrink() * violations[i]->flexBaseContentSize;
1459 // totalWeightedFlexShrink can be negative when we exceed the precision of
1460 // a double when we initially calcuate totalWeightedFlexShrink. We then
1461 // subtract each child's weighted flex shrink with full precision, now
1462 // leading to a negative result. See
1463 // css3/flexbox/large-flex-shrink-assert.html
1464 totalWeightedFlexShrink = std::max(totalWeightedFlexShrink, 0.0);
1465 violations[i]->frozen = true;
1466 }
1467}
1468
1469void RenderFlexibleBox::freezeInflexibleItems(FlexSign flexSign, Vector<FlexItem>& children, LayoutUnit& remainingFreeSpace, double& totalFlexGrow, double& totalFlexShrink, double& totalWeightedFlexShrink)
1470{
1471 // Per https://drafts.csswg.org/css-flexbox/#resolve-flexible-lengths step 2,
1472 // we freeze all items with a flex factor of 0 as well as those with a min/max
1473 // size violation.
1474 Vector<FlexItem*> newInflexibleItems;
1475 for (size_t i = 0; i < children.size(); ++i) {
1476 FlexItem& flexItem = children[i];
1477 const auto& child = flexItem.box;
1478 ASSERT(!flexItem.box.isOutOfFlowPositioned());
1479 ASSERT(!flexItem.frozen);
1480 float flexFactor = (flexSign == PositiveFlexibility) ? child.style().flexGrow() : child.style().flexShrink();
1481 if (!flexFactor || (flexSign == PositiveFlexibility && flexItem.flexBaseContentSize > flexItem.hypotheticalMainContentSize) || (flexSign == NegativeFlexibility && flexItem.flexBaseContentSize < flexItem.hypotheticalMainContentSize)) {
1482 flexItem.flexedContentSize = flexItem.hypotheticalMainContentSize;
1483 newInflexibleItems.append(&flexItem);
1484 }
1485 }
1486 freezeViolations(newInflexibleItems, remainingFreeSpace, totalFlexGrow, totalFlexShrink, totalWeightedFlexShrink);
1487}
1488
1489// Returns true if we successfully ran the algorithm and sized the flex items.
1490bool RenderFlexibleBox::resolveFlexibleLengths(FlexSign flexSign, Vector<FlexItem>& children, LayoutUnit initialFreeSpace, LayoutUnit& remainingFreeSpace, double& totalFlexGrow, double& totalFlexShrink, double& totalWeightedFlexShrink)
1491{
1492 LayoutUnit totalViolation;
1493 LayoutUnit usedFreeSpace;
1494 Vector<FlexItem*> minViolations;
1495 Vector<FlexItem*> maxViolations;
1496
1497 double sumFlexFactors = (flexSign == PositiveFlexibility) ? totalFlexGrow : totalFlexShrink;
1498 if (sumFlexFactors > 0 && sumFlexFactors < 1) {
1499 LayoutUnit fractional(initialFreeSpace * sumFlexFactors);
1500 if (fractional.abs() < remainingFreeSpace.abs())
1501 remainingFreeSpace = fractional;
1502 }
1503
1504 for (size_t i = 0; i < children.size(); ++i) {
1505 FlexItem& flexItem = children[i];
1506 auto& child = flexItem.box;
1507
1508 // This check also covers out-of-flow children.
1509 if (flexItem.frozen)
1510 continue;
1511
1512 LayoutUnit childSize = flexItem.flexBaseContentSize;
1513 double extraSpace = 0;
1514 if (remainingFreeSpace > 0 && totalFlexGrow > 0 && flexSign == PositiveFlexibility && std::isfinite(totalFlexGrow))
1515 extraSpace = remainingFreeSpace * child.style().flexGrow() / totalFlexGrow;
1516 else if (remainingFreeSpace < 0 && totalWeightedFlexShrink > 0 && flexSign == NegativeFlexibility && std::isfinite(totalWeightedFlexShrink) && child.style().flexShrink())
1517 extraSpace = remainingFreeSpace * child.style().flexShrink() * flexItem.flexBaseContentSize / totalWeightedFlexShrink;
1518 if (std::isfinite(extraSpace))
1519 childSize += LayoutUnit::fromFloatRound(extraSpace);
1520
1521 LayoutUnit adjustedChildSize = flexItem.constrainSizeByMinMax(childSize);
1522 ASSERT(adjustedChildSize >= 0);
1523 flexItem.flexedContentSize = adjustedChildSize;
1524 usedFreeSpace += adjustedChildSize - flexItem.flexBaseContentSize;
1525
1526 LayoutUnit violation = adjustedChildSize - childSize;
1527 if (violation > 0)
1528 minViolations.append(&flexItem);
1529 else if (violation < 0)
1530 maxViolations.append(&flexItem);
1531 totalViolation += violation;
1532 }
1533
1534 if (totalViolation)
1535 freezeViolations(totalViolation < 0 ? maxViolations : minViolations, remainingFreeSpace, totalFlexGrow, totalFlexShrink, totalWeightedFlexShrink);
1536 else
1537 remainingFreeSpace -= usedFreeSpace;
1538
1539 return !totalViolation;
1540}
1541
1542static LayoutUnit initialJustifyContentOffset(LayoutUnit availableFreeSpace, ContentPosition justifyContent, ContentDistribution justifyContentDistribution, unsigned numberOfChildren)
1543{
1544 if (justifyContent == ContentPosition::FlexEnd)
1545 return availableFreeSpace;
1546 if (justifyContent == ContentPosition::Center)
1547 return availableFreeSpace / 2;
1548 if (justifyContentDistribution == ContentDistribution::SpaceAround) {
1549 if (availableFreeSpace > 0 && numberOfChildren)
1550 return availableFreeSpace / (2 * numberOfChildren);
1551 else
1552 return availableFreeSpace / 2;
1553 }
1554 if (justifyContentDistribution == ContentDistribution::SpaceEvenly) {
1555 if (availableFreeSpace > 0 && numberOfChildren)
1556 return availableFreeSpace / (numberOfChildren + 1);
1557 // Fallback to 'center'
1558 return availableFreeSpace / 2;
1559 }
1560 return 0;
1561}
1562
1563static LayoutUnit justifyContentSpaceBetweenChildren(LayoutUnit availableFreeSpace, ContentDistribution justifyContentDistribution, unsigned numberOfChildren)
1564{
1565 if (availableFreeSpace > 0 && numberOfChildren > 1) {
1566 if (justifyContentDistribution == ContentDistribution::SpaceBetween)
1567 return availableFreeSpace / (numberOfChildren - 1);
1568 if (justifyContentDistribution == ContentDistribution::SpaceAround)
1569 return availableFreeSpace / numberOfChildren;
1570 if (justifyContentDistribution == ContentDistribution::SpaceEvenly)
1571 return availableFreeSpace / (numberOfChildren + 1);
1572 }
1573 return 0;
1574}
1575
1576static LayoutUnit alignmentOffset(LayoutUnit availableFreeSpace, ItemPosition position, LayoutUnit ascent, LayoutUnit maxAscent, bool isWrapReverse)
1577{
1578 switch (position) {
1579 case ItemPosition::Legacy:
1580 case ItemPosition::Auto:
1581 case ItemPosition::Normal:
1582 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1583 break;
1584 case ItemPosition::Stretch:
1585 // Actual stretching must be handled by the caller. Since wrap-reverse
1586 // flips cross start and cross end, stretch children should be aligned
1587 // with the cross end. This matters because applyStretchAlignment
1588 // doesn't always stretch or stretch fully (explicit cross size given, or
1589 // stretching constrained by max-height/max-width). For flex-start and
1590 // flex-end this is handled by alignmentForChild().
1591 if (isWrapReverse)
1592 return availableFreeSpace;
1593 break;
1594 case ItemPosition::FlexStart:
1595 break;
1596 case ItemPosition::FlexEnd:
1597 return availableFreeSpace;
1598 case ItemPosition::Center:
1599 return availableFreeSpace / 2;
1600 case ItemPosition::Baseline:
1601 // FIXME: If we get here in columns, we want the use the descent, except
1602 // we currently can't get the ascent/descent of orthogonal children.
1603 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=98076
1604 return maxAscent - ascent;
1605 case ItemPosition::LastBaseline:
1606 case ItemPosition::SelfStart:
1607 case ItemPosition::SelfEnd:
1608 case ItemPosition::Start:
1609 case ItemPosition::End:
1610 case ItemPosition::Left:
1611 case ItemPosition::Right:
1612 // FIXME: Implement the extended grammar, enabled when the Grid Layout
1613 // feature was enabled by default.
1614 break;
1615 }
1616 return 0;
1617}

1620{
1621 if (mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis(child))
1622 child.setOverridingLogicalWidth(childPreferredSize + child.borderAndPaddingLogicalWidth());
1623 else
1624 child.setOverridingLogicalHeight(childPreferredSize + child.borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight());

1627LayoutUnit RenderFlexibleBox::staticMainAxisPositionForPositionedChild(const RenderBox& child)
1628{
1629 const LayoutUnit availableSpace = mainAxisContentExtent(contentLogicalHeight()) - mainAxisExtentForChild(child);
1630
1631 ContentPosition position = style().resolvedJustifyContentPosition(contentAlignmentNormalBehavior());
1632 ContentDistribution distribution = style().resolvedJustifyContentDistribution(contentAlignmentNormalBehavior());
1633 LayoutUnit offset = initialJustifyContentOffset(availableSpace, position, distribution, 1);
1634 if (style().flexDirection() == FlexDirection::RowReverse || style().flexDirection() == FlexDirection::ColumnReverse)
1635 offset = availableSpace - offset;
1636 return offset;
1637}

1655bool RenderFlexibleBox::setStaticPositionForPositionedLayout(const RenderBox& child)
1656{
1657 bool positionChanged = false;
1658 auto* childLayer = child.layer();
1659 if (child.style().hasStaticInlinePosition(style().isHorizontalWritingMode())) {
1660 LayoutUnit inlinePosition = staticInlinePositionForPositionedChild(child);
1661 if (childLayer->staticInlinePosition() != inlinePosition) {
1662 childLayer->setStaticInlinePosition(inlinePosition);
1663 positionChanged = true;
1664 }
1665 }
1666 if (child.style().hasStaticBlockPosition(style().isHorizontalWritingMode())) {
1667 LayoutUnit blockPosition = staticBlockPositionForPositionedChild(child);
1668 if (childLayer->staticBlockPosition() != blockPosition) {
1669 childLayer->setStaticBlockPosition(blockPosition);
1670 positionChanged = true;
1671 }
1672 }
1673 return positionChanged;
1674}

1676// This refers to https://drafts.csswg.org/css-flexbox-1/#definite-sizes, section 1).

1678{

1685void RenderFlexibleBox::prepareChildForPositionedLayout(RenderBox& child)
1686{
1687 ASSERT(child.isOutOfFlowPositioned());
1688 child.containingBlock()->insertPositionedObject(child);
1689 auto* childLayer = child.layer();
1690 LayoutUnit staticInlinePosition = flowAwareBorderStart() + flowAwarePaddingStart();
1691 if (childLayer->staticInlinePosition() != staticInlinePosition) {
1692 childLayer->setStaticInlinePosition(staticInlinePosition);
1693 if (child.style().hasStaticInlinePosition(style().isHorizontalWritingMode()))
1694 child.setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
1695 }
1696
1697 LayoutUnit staticBlockPosition = flowAwareBorderBefore() + flowAwarePaddingBefore();
1698 if (childLayer->staticBlockPosition() != staticBlockPosition) {
1699 childLayer->setStaticBlockPosition(staticBlockPosition);
1700 if (child.style().hasStaticBlockPosition(style().isHorizontalWritingMode()))
1701 child.setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
1702 }
1703}

1705ItemPosition RenderFlexibleBox::alignmentForChild(const RenderBox& child) const
1706{
1707 ItemPosition align = child.style().resolvedAlignSelf(&style(), selfAlignmentNormalBehavior()).position();
1708 ASSERT(align != ItemPosition::Auto && align != ItemPosition::Normal);
1709
1710 if (align == ItemPosition::Baseline && !mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis(child))
1711 align = ItemPosition::FlexStart;
1712
1713 if (style().flexWrap() == FlexWrap::Reverse) {
1714 if (align == ItemPosition::FlexStart)
1715 align = ItemPosition::FlexEnd;
1716 else if (align == ItemPosition::FlexEnd)
1717 align = ItemPosition::FlexStart;
1718 }
1719
1720 return align;
1721}

1723void RenderFlexibleBox::resetAutoMarginsAndLogicalTopInCrossAxis(RenderBox& child)
1724{
1725 if (hasAutoMarginsInCrossAxis(child)) {
1726 child.updateLogicalHeight();
1727 if (isHorizontalFlow()) {
1728 if (child.style().marginTop().isAuto())
1729 child.setMarginTop(0_lu);
1730 if (child.style().marginBottom().isAuto())
1731 child.setMarginBottom(0_lu);
1732 } else {
1733 if (child.style().marginLeft().isAuto())
1734 child.setMarginLeft(0_lu);
1735 if (child.style().marginRight().isAuto())
1736 child.setMarginRight(0_lu);
1737 }
1738 }

1740
1741bool RenderFlexibleBox::needToStretchChildLogicalHeight(const RenderBox& child) const
1742{
1743 // This function is a little bit magical. It relies on the fact that blocks
1744 // intrinsically "stretch" themselves in their inline axis, i.e. a <div> has
1745 // an implicit width: 100%. So the child will automatically stretch if our
1746 // cross axis is the child's inline axis. That's the case if:
1747 // - We are horizontal and the child is in vertical writing mode
1748 // - We are vertical and the child is in horizontal writing mode
1749 // Otherwise, we need to stretch if the cross axis size is auto.
1750 if (alignmentForChild(child) != ItemPosition::Stretch)
1751 return false;
1752
1753 if (isHorizontalFlow() != child.style().isHorizontalWritingMode())
1754 return false;
1755
1756 // Aspect ratio is properly handled by RenderReplaced during layout.
1757 if (child.isRenderReplaced() && childHasAspectRatio(child))
1758 return false;
1759
1760 return child.style().logicalHeight().isAuto();
1761}
1762
1763bool RenderFlexibleBox::childHasIntrinsicMainAxisSize(const RenderBox& child)
1764{
1765 if (mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis(child))
1766 return false;
1767
1768 Length childFlexBasis = flexBasisForChild(child);
1769 Length childMinSize = mainSizeLengthForChild(MinSize, child);
1770 Length childMaxSize = mainSizeLengthForChild(MaxSize, child);
1771 // FIXME: we must run childMainSizeIsDefinite() because it might end up calling computePercentageLogicalHeight()
1772 // which has some side effects like calling addPercentHeightDescendant() for example so it is not possible to skip
1773 // the call for example by moving it to the end of the conditional expression. This is error-prone and we should
1774 // refactor computePercentageLogicalHeight() at some point so that it only computes stuff without those side effects.
1775 if (!childMainSizeIsDefinite(child, childFlexBasis) || childMinSize.isIntrinsic() || childMaxSize.isIntrinsic())
1776 return true;
1777
1778 if (shouldApplyMinSizeAutoForChild(child))
1779 return true;
1780
1781 return false;
1782}
1783
1784Overflow RenderFlexibleBox::mainAxisOverflowForChild(const RenderBox& child) const
1785{
1786 if (isHorizontalFlow())
1787 return child.style().overflowX();
1788 return child.style().overflowY();
1789}
1790
1791Overflow RenderFlexibleBox::crossAxisOverflowForChild(const RenderBox& child) const

1798bool RenderFlexibleBox::childHasPercentHeightDescendants(const RenderBox& renderer) const
1799{
1800 // FIXME: This function can be removed soon after webkit.org/b/204318 is fixed. Evaluate whether the
1801 // skipContainingBlockForPercentHeightCalculation() check below should be moved to the caller in that case.
1802 if (!is<RenderBlock>(renderer))
1803 return false;
1804 auto& renderBlock = downcast<RenderBlock>(renderer);
1805
1806 // FlexibleBoxImpl's like RenderButton might wrap their children in anonymous blocks. Those anonymous blocks are
1807 // skipped for percentage height calculations in RenderBox::computePercentageLogicalHeight() and thus
1808 // addPercentHeightDescendant() is never called for them. This means that this method would always wrongly
1809 // return false for a child of a <button> with a percentage height.
1810 if (hasPercentHeightDescendants() && skipContainingBlockForPercentHeightCalculation(renderer, isHorizontalWritingMode() != renderer.isHorizontalWritingMode())) {
1811 auto& descendants = *percentHeightDescendants();
1812 for (auto* descendant : descendants) {
1813 if (renderBlock.isContainingBlockAncestorFor(*descendant))
1814 return true;
1815 }
1816 }
1817
1818 if (!renderBlock.hasPercentHeightDescendants())
1819 return false;
1820
1821 auto* percentHeightDescendants = renderBlock.percentHeightDescendants();
1822 if (!percentHeightDescendants)
1823 return false;
1824
1825 for (auto it = percentHeightDescendants->begin(), end = percentHeightDescendants->end(); it != end; ++it) {
1826 bool hasOutOfFlowAncestor = false;
1827 for (auto* ancestor = (*it)->containingBlock(); ancestor && ancestor != &renderBlock; ancestor = ancestor->containingBlock()) {
1828 if (ancestor->isOutOfFlowPositioned()) {
1829 hasOutOfFlowAncestor = true;
1830 break;
1831 }
1832 }
1833 if (!hasOutOfFlowAncestor)
1834 return true;
1835 }
1836 return false;
1837}

1839void RenderFlexibleBox::layoutAndPlaceChildren(LayoutUnit& crossAxisOffset, Vector<FlexItem>& children, LayoutUnit availableFreeSpace, bool relayoutChildren, Vector<LineContext>& lineContexts, LayoutUnit gapBetweenItems)
1840{
1841 ContentPosition position = style().resolvedJustifyContentPosition(contentAlignmentNormalBehavior());
1842 ContentDistribution distribution = style().resolvedJustifyContentDistribution(contentAlignmentNormalBehavior());
1843
1844 LayoutUnit autoMarginOffset = autoMarginOffsetInMainAxis(children, availableFreeSpace);
1845 LayoutUnit mainAxisOffset = flowAwareBorderStart() + flowAwarePaddingStart();
1846 mainAxisOffset += initialJustifyContentOffset(availableFreeSpace, position, distribution, children.size());
1847 if (style().flexDirection() == FlexDirection::RowReverse)
1848 mainAxisOffset += isHorizontalFlow() ? verticalScrollbarWidth() : horizontalScrollbarHeight();
1849
1850 LayoutUnit totalMainExtent = mainAxisExtent();
1851 LayoutUnit maxAscent, maxDescent; // Used when align-items: baseline.
1852 LayoutUnit maxChildCrossAxisExtent;
1853 bool shouldFlipMainAxis = !isColumnFlow() && !isLeftToRightFlow();
1854 for (size_t i = 0; i < children.size(); ++i) {
1855 const auto& flexItem = children[i];
1856 auto& child = flexItem.box;
1857
1858 ASSERT(!flexItem.box.isOutOfFlowPositioned());
1859
1860 setOverridingMainSizeForChild(child, flexItem.flexedContentSize);
1861 // The flexed content size and the override size include the scrollbar
1862 // width, so we need to compare to the size including the scrollbar.
1863 // TODO(cbiesinger): Should it include the scrollbar?
1864 if (flexItem.flexedContentSize != mainAxisContentExtentForChildIncludingScrollbar(child))
1865 child.setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
1866 else {
1867 // To avoid double applying margin changes in
1868 // updateAutoMarginsInCrossAxis, we reset the margins here.
1869 resetAutoMarginsAndLogicalTopInCrossAxis(child);
1870 }
1871 // We may have already forced relayout for orthogonal flowing children in
1872 // computeInnerFlexBaseSizeForChild.
1873 bool forceChildRelayout = relayoutChildren && !m_relaidOutChildren.contains(&child);
1874 if (!forceChildRelayout && childHasPercentHeightDescendants(child)) {
1875 // Have to force another relayout even though the child is sized
1876 // correctly, because its descendants are not sized correctly yet. Our
1877 // previous layout of the child was done without an override height set.
1878 // So, redo it here.
1879 forceChildRelayout = true;
1880 }
1881 updateBlockChildDirtyBitsBeforeLayout(forceChildRelayout, child);
1882 if (!child.needsLayout())
1883 child.markForPaginationRelayoutIfNeeded();
1884 if (child.needsLayout())
1885 m_relaidOutChildren.add(&child);
1886 child.layoutIfNeeded();
1887 if (!flexItem.everHadLayout && child.checkForRepaintDuringLayout()) {
1888 child.repaint();
1889 child.repaintOverhangingFloats(true);
1890 }
1891
1892 updateAutoMarginsInMainAxis(child, autoMarginOffset);
1893
1894 LayoutUnit childCrossAxisMarginBoxExtent;
1895 if (alignmentForChild(child) == ItemPosition::Baseline && !hasAutoMarginsInCrossAxis(child)) {
1896 LayoutUnit ascent = marginBoxAscentForChild(child);
1897 LayoutUnit descent = (crossAxisMarginExtentForChild(child) + crossAxisExtentForChild(child)) - ascent;
1898
1899 maxAscent = std::max(maxAscent, ascent);
1900 maxDescent = std::max(maxDescent, descent);
1901
1902 // FIXME: Take scrollbar into account
1903 childCrossAxisMarginBoxExtent = maxAscent + maxDescent;
1904 } else
1905 childCrossAxisMarginBoxExtent = crossAxisIntrinsicExtentForChild(child) + crossAxisMarginExtentForChild(child);
1906
1907 if (!isColumnFlow())
1908 setLogicalHeight(std::max(logicalHeight(), crossAxisOffset + flowAwareBorderAfter() + flowAwarePaddingAfter() + childCrossAxisMarginBoxExtent + crossAxisScrollbarExtent()));
1909 maxChildCrossAxisExtent = std::max(maxChildCrossAxisExtent, childCrossAxisMarginBoxExtent);
1910
1911 mainAxisOffset += flowAwareMarginStartForChild(child);
1912
1913 LayoutUnit childMainExtent = mainAxisExtentForChild(child);
1914 // In an RTL column situation, this will apply the margin-right/margin-end
1915 // on the left. This will be fixed later in flipForRightToLeftColumn.
1916 LayoutPoint childLocation(shouldFlipMainAxis ? totalMainExtent - mainAxisOffset - childMainExtent : mainAxisOffset, crossAxisOffset + flowAwareMarginBeforeForChild(child));
1917 setFlowAwareLocationForChild(child, childLocation);
1918 mainAxisOffset += childMainExtent + flowAwareMarginEndForChild(child);
1919
1920 if (i != children.size() - 1) {
1921 // The last item does not get extra space added.
1922 mainAxisOffset += justifyContentSpaceBetweenChildren(availableFreeSpace, distribution, children.size()) + gapBetweenItems;
1923 }
1924
1925 // FIXME: Deal with pagination.
1926 }
1927
1928 if (isColumnFlow())
1929 setLogicalHeight(std::max(logicalHeight(), mainAxisOffset + flowAwareBorderEnd() + flowAwarePaddingEnd() + scrollbarLogicalHeight()));
1930
1931 if (style().flexDirection() == FlexDirection::ColumnReverse) {
1932 // We have to do an extra pass for column-reverse to reposition the flex
1933 // items since the start depends on the height of the flexbox, which we
1934 // only know after we've positioned all the flex items.
1935 updateLogicalHeight();
1936 layoutColumnReverse(children, crossAxisOffset, availableFreeSpace);
1937 }
1938
1939 if (m_numberOfInFlowChildrenOnFirstLine == -1)
1940 m_numberOfInFlowChildrenOnFirstLine = children.size();
1941 lineContexts.append(LineContext(crossAxisOffset, maxChildCrossAxisExtent, maxAscent, WTFMove(children)));
1942 crossAxisOffset += maxChildCrossAxisExtent;
1943}
1944
1945void RenderFlexibleBox::layoutColumnReverse(const Vector<FlexItem>& children, LayoutUnit crossAxisOffset, LayoutUnit availableFreeSpace)
1946{
1947 ContentPosition position = style().resolvedJustifyContentPosition(contentAlignmentNormalBehavior());
1948 ContentDistribution distribution = style().resolvedJustifyContentDistribution(contentAlignmentNormalBehavior());
1949
1950 // This is similar to the logic in layoutAndPlaceChildren, except we place
1951 // the children starting from the end of the flexbox. We also don't need to
1952 // layout anything since we're just moving the children to a new position.
1953 LayoutUnit mainAxisOffset = logicalHeight() - flowAwareBorderEnd() - flowAwarePaddingEnd();
1954 mainAxisOffset -= initialJustifyContentOffset(availableFreeSpace, position, distribution, children.size());
1955 mainAxisOffset -= isHorizontalFlow() ? verticalScrollbarWidth() : horizontalScrollbarHeight();
1956
1957 for (size_t i = 0; i < children.size(); ++i) {
1958 auto& child = children[i].box;
1959 ASSERT(!child.isOutOfFlowPositioned());
1960 mainAxisOffset -= mainAxisExtentForChild(child) + flowAwareMarginEndForChild(child);
1961 setFlowAwareLocationForChild(child, LayoutPoint(mainAxisOffset, crossAxisOffset + flowAwareMarginBeforeForChild(child)));
1962 mainAxisOffset -= flowAwareMarginStartForChild(child);
1963 mainAxisOffset -= justifyContentSpaceBetweenChildren(availableFreeSpace, distribution, children.size());
1964 }
1965}
1966
1967static LayoutUnit initialAlignContentOffset(LayoutUnit availableFreeSpace, ContentPosition alignContent, ContentDistribution alignContentDistribution, unsigned numberOfLines)
1968{
1969 if (alignContent == ContentPosition::FlexEnd)
1970 return availableFreeSpace;
1971 if (alignContent == ContentPosition::Center)
1972 return availableFreeSpace / 2;
1973 if (alignContentDistribution == ContentDistribution::SpaceAround) {
1974 if (availableFreeSpace > 0 && numberOfLines)
1975 return availableFreeSpace / (2 * numberOfLines);
1976 if (availableFreeSpace < 0)
1977 return availableFreeSpace / 2;
1978 }
1979 if (alignContentDistribution == ContentDistribution::SpaceEvenly) {
1980 if (availableFreeSpace > 0)
1981 return availableFreeSpace / (numberOfLines + 1);
1982 // Fallback to 'center'
1983 return availableFreeSpace / 2;
1984 }
1985 return 0_lu;
1986}
1987
1988static LayoutUnit alignContentSpaceBetweenChildren(LayoutUnit availableFreeSpace, ContentDistribution alignContentDistribution, unsigned numberOfLines)
1989{
1990 if (availableFreeSpace > 0 && numberOfLines > 1) {
1991 if (alignContentDistribution == ContentDistribution::SpaceBetween)
1992 return availableFreeSpace / (numberOfLines - 1);
1993 if (alignContentDistribution == ContentDistribution::SpaceAround || alignContentDistribution == ContentDistribution::Stretch)
1994 return availableFreeSpace / numberOfLines;
1995 if (alignContentDistribution == ContentDistribution::SpaceEvenly)
1996 return availableFreeSpace / (numberOfLines + 1);
1997 }
1998 return 0_lu;
1999}

2001void RenderFlexibleBox::alignFlexLines(Vector<LineContext>& lineContexts, LayoutUnit gapBetweenLines)
2002{
2003 if (lineContexts.isEmpty() || !isMultiline())
2004 return;
2005
2006 ContentPosition position = style().resolvedAlignContentPosition(contentAlignmentNormalBehavior());
2007 ContentDistribution distribution = style().resolvedAlignContentDistribution(contentAlignmentNormalBehavior());
2008
2009 if (position == ContentPosition::FlexStart && !gapBetweenLines)
2010 return;
2011
2012 size_t numLines = lineContexts.size();
2013 LayoutUnit availableCrossAxisSpace = crossAxisContentExtent() - (numLines - 1) * gapBetweenLines;
2014 for (size_t i = 0; i < numLines; ++i)
2015 availableCrossAxisSpace -= lineContexts[i].crossAxisExtent;
2016
2017 LayoutUnit lineOffset = initialAlignContentOffset(availableCrossAxisSpace, position, distribution, numLines);
2018 for (unsigned lineNumber = 0; lineNumber < numLines; ++lineNumber) {
2019 LineContext& lineContext = lineContexts[lineNumber];
2020 lineContext.crossAxisOffset += lineOffset;
2021 for (size_t childNumber = 0; childNumber < lineContext.flexItems.size(); ++childNumber) {
2022 FlexItem& flexItem = lineContext.flexItems[childNumber];
2023 adjustAlignmentForChild(flexItem.box, lineOffset);
2024 }
2025
2026 if (distribution == ContentDistribution::Stretch && availableCrossAxisSpace > 0)
2027 lineContexts[lineNumber].crossAxisExtent += availableCrossAxisSpace / static_cast<unsigned>(numLines);
2028
2029 lineOffset += alignContentSpaceBetweenChildren(availableCrossAxisSpace, distribution, numLines) + gapBetweenLines;
2030 }
2031}
