2033void RenderFlexibleBox::adjustAlignmentForChild(RenderBox& child, LayoutUnit delta)
2034{
2035 ASSERT(!child.isOutOfFlowPositioned());
2036 setFlowAwareLocationForChild(child, flowAwareLocationForChild(child) + LayoutSize(0_lu, delta));
2037}
2038
2039void RenderFlexibleBox::alignChildren(const Vector<LineContext>& lineContexts)
2040{
2041 // Keep track of the space between the baseline edge and the after edge of
2042 // the box for each line.
2043 Vector<LayoutUnit> minMarginAfterBaselines;
2044
2045 for (size_t lineNumber = 0; lineNumber < lineContexts.size(); ++lineNumber) {
2046 const LineContext& lineContext = lineContexts[lineNumber];
2047
2048 LayoutUnit minMarginAfterBaseline = LayoutUnit::max();
2049 LayoutUnit lineCrossAxisExtent = lineContext.crossAxisExtent;
2050 LayoutUnit maxAscent = lineContext.maxAscent;
2051
2052 for (size_t childNumber = 0; childNumber < lineContext.flexItems.size(); ++childNumber) {
2053 const auto& flexItem = lineContext.flexItems[childNumber];
2054 ASSERT(!flexItem.box.isOutOfFlowPositioned());
2055
2056 if (updateAutoMarginsInCrossAxis(flexItem.box, std::max(0_lu, availableAlignmentSpaceForChild(lineCrossAxisExtent, flexItem.box))))
2057 continue;
2058
2059 ItemPosition position = alignmentForChild(flexItem.box);
2060 if (position == ItemPosition::Stretch)
2061 applyStretchAlignmentToChild(flexItem.box, lineCrossAxisExtent);
2062 LayoutUnit availableSpace = availableAlignmentSpaceForChild(lineCrossAxisExtent, flexItem.box);
2063 LayoutUnit offset = alignmentOffset(availableSpace, position, marginBoxAscentForChild(flexItem.box), maxAscent, style().flexWrap() == FlexWrap::Reverse);
2064 adjustAlignmentForChild(flexItem.box, offset);
2065 if (position == ItemPosition::Baseline && style().flexWrap() == FlexWrap::Reverse)
2066 minMarginAfterBaseline = std::min(minMarginAfterBaseline, availableAlignmentSpaceForChild(lineCrossAxisExtent, flexItem.box) - offset);
2067 }
2068
2069 minMarginAfterBaselines.append(minMarginAfterBaseline);
2070 }
2071
2072 if (style().flexWrap() != FlexWrap::Reverse)
2073 return;
2074
2075 // wrap-reverse flips the cross axis start and end. For baseline alignment,
2076 // this means we need to align the after edge of baseline elements with the
2077 // after edge of the flex line.
2078 for (size_t lineNumber = 0; lineNumber < lineContexts.size(); ++lineNumber) {
2079 const LineContext& lineContext = lineContexts[lineNumber];
2080 LayoutUnit minMarginAfterBaseline = minMarginAfterBaselines[lineNumber];
2081 for (size_t childNumber = 0; childNumber < lineContext.flexItems.size(); ++childNumber) {
2082 const auto& flexItem = lineContext.flexItems[childNumber];
2083 if (alignmentForChild(flexItem.box) == ItemPosition::Baseline && !hasAutoMarginsInCrossAxis(flexItem.box) && minMarginAfterBaseline)
2084 adjustAlignmentForChild(flexItem.box, minMarginAfterBaseline);
2085 }
2086 }
2087}

2089void RenderFlexibleBox::applyStretchAlignmentToChild(RenderBox& child, LayoutUnit lineCrossAxisExtent)
2090{
2091 if (mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis(child) && child.style().logicalHeight().isAuto()) {
2092 LayoutUnit stretchedLogicalHeight = std::max(child.borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight(),
2093 lineCrossAxisExtent - crossAxisMarginExtentForChild(child));
2094 ASSERT(!child.needsLayout());
2095 LayoutUnit desiredLogicalHeight = child.constrainLogicalHeightByMinMax(stretchedLogicalHeight, cachedChildIntrinsicContentLogicalHeight(child));
2096
2097 // FIXME: Can avoid laying out here in some cases. See https://webkit.org/b/87905.
2098 bool childNeedsRelayout = desiredLogicalHeight != child.logicalHeight();
2099 if (child.isRenderBlock() && downcast<RenderBlock>(child).hasPercentHeightDescendants() && m_relaidOutChildren.contains(&child)) {
2100 // Have to force another relayout even though the child is sized
2101 // correctly, because its descendants are not sized correctly yet. Our
2102 // previous layout of the child was done without an override height set.
2103 // So, redo it here.
2104 childNeedsRelayout = true;
2105 }
2106 if (childNeedsRelayout || !child.hasOverridingLogicalHeight())
2107 child.setOverridingLogicalHeight(desiredLogicalHeight);
2108 if (childNeedsRelayout) {
2109 SetForScope<bool> resetChildLogicalHeight(m_shouldResetChildLogicalHeightBeforeLayout, true);
2110 // We cache the child's intrinsic content logical height to avoid it being
2111 // reset to the stretched height.
2112 // FIXME: This is fragile. RenderBoxes should be smart enough to
2113 // determine their intrinsic content logical height correctly even when
2114 // there's an overrideHeight.
2115 LayoutUnit childIntrinsicContentLogicalHeight = cachedChildIntrinsicContentLogicalHeight(child);
2116 child.setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
2117
2118 // Don't use layoutChildIfNeeded to avoid setting cross axis cached size twice.
2119 child.layoutIfNeeded();
2120
2121 setCachedChildIntrinsicContentLogicalHeight(child, childIntrinsicContentLogicalHeight);
2122 }
2123 } else if (!mainAxisIsChildInlineAxis(child) && child.style().logicalWidth().isAuto()) {
2124 LayoutUnit childWidth = std::max(0_lu, lineCrossAxisExtent - crossAxisMarginExtentForChild(child));
2125 childWidth = child.constrainLogicalWidthInFragmentByMinMax(childWidth, crossAxisContentExtent(), *this, nullptr);
2126
2127 if (childWidth != child.logicalWidth()) {
2128 child.setOverridingLogicalWidth(childWidth);
2129 child.setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
2130 child.layoutIfNeeded();
2131 }
2132 }
2133}

2135void RenderFlexibleBox::flipForRightToLeftColumn(const Vector<LineContext>& lineContexts)
2136{
2137 if (style().isLeftToRightDirection() || !isColumnFlow())
2138 return;
2139
2140 LayoutUnit crossExtent = crossAxisExtent();
2141 for (size_t lineNumber = 0; lineNumber < lineContexts.size(); ++lineNumber) {
2142 const LineContext& lineContext = lineContexts[lineNumber];
2143 for (size_t childNumber = 0; childNumber < lineContext.flexItems.size(); ++childNumber) {
2144 const auto& flexItem = lineContext.flexItems[childNumber];
2145 ASSERT(!flexItem.box.isOutOfFlowPositioned());
2146
2147 LayoutPoint location = flowAwareLocationForChild(flexItem.box);
2148 // For vertical flows, setFlowAwareLocationForChild will transpose x and
2149 // y, so using the y axis for a column cross axis extent is correct.
2150 location.setY(crossExtent - crossAxisExtentForChild(flexItem.box) - location.y());
2151 if (!isHorizontalWritingMode())
2152 location.move(LayoutSize(0, -horizontalScrollbarHeight()));
2153 setFlowAwareLocationForChild(flexItem.box, location);
2154 }
2155 }
2156}

2158void RenderFlexibleBox::flipForWrapReverse(const Vector<LineContext>& lineContexts, LayoutUnit crossAxisStartEdge)
2159{
2160 LayoutUnit contentExtent = crossAxisContentExtent();
2161 for (size_t lineNumber = 0; lineNumber < lineContexts.size(); ++lineNumber) {
2162 const LineContext& lineContext = lineContexts[lineNumber];
2163 for (size_t childNumber = 0; childNumber < lineContext.flexItems.size(); ++childNumber) {
2164 const auto& flexItem = lineContext.flexItems[childNumber];
2165 LayoutUnit lineCrossAxisExtent = lineContexts[lineNumber].crossAxisExtent;
2166 LayoutUnit originalOffset = lineContexts[lineNumber].crossAxisOffset - crossAxisStartEdge;
2167 LayoutUnit newOffset = contentExtent - originalOffset - lineCrossAxisExtent;
2168 adjustAlignmentForChild(flexItem.box, newOffset - originalOffset);
2169 }
2170 }

2191LayoutUnit RenderFlexibleBox::computeGap(RenderFlexibleBox::GapType gapType) const
2192{
2193 // row-gap is used for gaps between flex items in column flows or for gaps between lines in row flows.
2194 bool usesRowGap = (gapType == GapType::BetweenItems) == isColumnFlow();
2195 auto& gapLength = usesRowGap ? style().rowGap() : style().columnGap();
2196 if (LIKELY(gapLength.isNormal()))
2197 return { };
2198
2199 auto availableSize = usesRowGap ? availableLogicalHeightForPercentageComputation().value_or(0_lu) : contentLogicalWidth();
2200 return minimumValueForLength(gapLength.length(), availableSize);
2201}
